>> negative number of anything.

Steve> Perhaps not, but saying "I have a negative amount of money." is
Steve> an acceptable way of saying "I am in debt." in my opinion.

Ah, I was hoping that someone would make this comment!  Suppose that
we do hold that a negative balance is a debt.  A debt to who?  The
Bank seems to be the obvious choice.  Then what is a negative balance
in the Bank?  A debt to the Bank?  That's absurd!

The "negative balance == debt" concept is absurd when there is no
central lending authority.  We have no central lending authority.

